1
00:00:10,080 --> 00:00:11,120
Wait.

2
00:00:11,120 --> 00:00:12,880
Isn't this a bit overprotective?

3
00:00:12,880 --> 00:00:14,200
How about I tie you back
to the hospital?

4
00:00:14,640 --> 00:00:15,440
Boss,

5
00:00:16,040 --> 00:00:16,920
Shen Hao has been sentenced

6
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:18,000
to serve 15 years in prison.

7
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:19,680
Even though Shen Tingyuan had a stroke,

8
00:00:19,680 --> 00:00:21,600
he still has to undergo
a financial investigation.

9
00:00:21,640 --> 00:00:23,800
He'll likely spend
the rest of his life in jail.

10
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:24,960
Also,

11
00:00:24,960 --> 00:00:27,080
your father's case
from back then will be retried.

12
00:00:35,640 --> 00:00:36,440
Wanxin,

13
00:00:37,440 --> 00:00:39,680
Shen Hao's crimes
have nothing to do with you.

14
00:00:40,120 --> 00:00:41,200
Please don't be afraid.

15
00:00:44,080 --> 00:00:44,880
With you here,

16
00:00:45,680 --> 00:00:46,480
I'm not afraid.

17
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:55,040
What's wrong? Does it hurt?

18
00:00:55,280 --> 00:00:55,840
It's nothing.

19
00:00:55,960 --> 00:00:56,520
Does it hurt?

20
00:00:56,640 --> 00:00:57,200
No.

21
00:00:58,240 --> 00:00:58,920
It doesn't hurt?

22
00:00:58,920 --> 00:00:59,600
It doesn't hurt.

23
00:00:59,880 --> 00:01:00,680
Let's go.

24
00:01:03,300 --> 00:01:07,340
=Echoes of Gang City=

25
00:01:07,460 --> 00:01:11,140
=Episode 27=
(The Gentleman and the Lady)

26
00:01:13,100 --> 00:01:15,780
(Engagement Certificate)

27
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:20,520
This is the item I've kept
in a temple in Shen City.

28
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:24,960
The 25th year of the Republic of China.

29
00:01:25,840 --> 00:01:26,800
Lin Shuyi.

30
00:01:28,360 --> 00:01:29,160
Shen Gu.

31
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:32,440
He was also called Shen Gu.

32
00:01:34,320 --> 00:01:35,640
I didn't expect them to sound the same.

33
00:01:36,760 --> 00:01:41,800
They were the benefactors
who saved my life back then.

34
00:01:45,620 --> 00:01:52,860
(East Asia Restaurant)

35
00:01:52,860 --> 00:01:53,440
Darn it.

36
00:01:53,450 --> 00:01:54,440
This tastes awful.

37
00:01:56,440 --> 00:01:58,360
You little brat,
watch where you're going!

38
00:01:59,040 --> 00:02:00,200
I'm talking to you!

39
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:01,320
You little rascal,

40
00:02:01,440 --> 00:02:02,600
you're even eating
scraps meant for dogs.

41
00:02:03,320 --> 00:02:04,240
What are you doing?

42
00:02:04,880 --> 00:02:05,960
Who are you?

43
00:02:06,520 --> 00:02:08,000
Do you need me to call the police?

44
00:02:08,570 --> 00:02:10,320
Spit it out quickly. This is too dirty.

45
00:02:13,320 --> 00:02:14,400
Mr. Shen, Miss Lin, what happened?

46
00:02:19,360 --> 00:02:20,160
What's wrong?

47
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:22,200
Boy.

48
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:22,920
Child.

49
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:24,280
What's wrong?

50
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:26,040
What is your name?

51
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:27,920
Come with us from now on.

52
00:02:28,320 --> 00:02:30,000
I'm the fourth child in my family.

53
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:32,120
Everyone at home calls me Xu Si.

54
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:34,160
When paths cross in the countryside,

55
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:36,040
every direction is a way out.

56
00:02:37,080 --> 00:02:37,880
From now on,

57
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:39,360
your name will be Xu Qianmo.

58
00:02:39,680 --> 00:02:40,320
How about that?

59
00:02:40,760 --> 00:02:42,000
Qianmo.

60
00:02:45,780 --> 00:02:48,780
(Record of Disaster-Stricken Children
in Shen City)

61
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:55,160
What are you looking at?

62
00:02:55,320 --> 00:02:56,400
You seem distracted.

63
00:02:57,700 --> 00:03:00,500
(Record of Disaster-Stricken Children
in Shen City)

64
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:04,840
I have both of you,

65
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,240
but what will happen to them?

66
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:12,120
There is an English-style
building on Avenue Joffre.

67
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:13,640
It's just sitting empty.

68
00:03:14,120 --> 00:03:16,840
Why not put up a bronze plaque
for a charitable children's home

69
00:03:17,320 --> 00:03:18,720
and let these children move in?

70
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:21,720
I knew it.

71
00:03:21,720 --> 00:03:24,000
Mr. Shen, you know my heart best.

72
00:03:25,040 --> 00:03:26,200
Then, I wonder

73
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:28,680
if this proposal gift

74
00:03:29,120 --> 00:03:30,440
is to your liking?

75
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:35,040
It's so beautiful.

76
00:03:35,320 --> 00:03:36,760
It's my favorite blue.

77
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:43,520
When we get married,

78
00:03:43,920 --> 00:03:46,200
I will also put your
favorite ring on your finger.

79
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:53,920
Okay.

80
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:04,240
(Chengyi Charitable Children's Home)
The shelters in the Concession are overcrowded.

81
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:07,160
We must thank your society
for taking in these children.

82
00:04:07,720 --> 00:04:08,920
This was Shuyi's wish.

83
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:10,840
Anyway, thank you.

84
00:04:12,240 --> 00:04:13,000
Slow down.

85
00:04:14,240 --> 00:04:15,040
Slow down.

86
00:04:16,320 --> 00:04:17,400
Don't run around.

87
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:21,520
Shuyi.

88
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:25,240
We can follow the Kunshan
Relief House's model to keep records.

89
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:28,720
We might as well add a school.

90
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:32,040
The kids at Xiangshan Charitable
Children's Home are learning beekeeping,

91
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:35,400
and the boys at Tushan Orphanage
are learning to carve glass.

92
00:04:36,400 --> 00:04:37,600
In these turbulent times,

93
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:41,720
it gives them a means
to survive in the future.

94
00:04:44,560 --> 00:04:46,720
Wasn't Qianmo raised very well by us?

95
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:47,640
Be good, Ni.

96
00:04:48,440 --> 00:04:49,760
With this,

97
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:52,060
you won't go hungry even if we're gone.

98
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:53,520
Once you're better,

99
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:55,240
I'll take you to the City God Temple

100
00:04:55,720 --> 00:04:57,640
to eat crab roe buns, okay?

101
00:04:57,800 --> 00:04:58,600
Okay.

102
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:01,520
Qianmo will be a role model
for all the children.

103
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:04,560
Mr. Shen, you look like

104
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:06,640
a teacher from St. John's College.

105
00:05:07,080 --> 00:05:08,320
The children like you very much.

106
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:11,120
I only want your affection, Miss Lin.

107
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:19,200
Gu,

108
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:21,640
the nation is in crisis,

109
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:22,600
and the country is shattered...

110
00:05:23,190 --> 00:05:23,940
Slow down.

111
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:26,800
This is all we can do.

112
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:28,720
But I still feel it's not enough.

113
00:05:29,200 --> 00:05:30,320
In times like these,

114
00:05:31,040 --> 00:05:32,800
all we can do is our best.

115
00:05:35,640 --> 00:05:36,640
As long as people are alive,

116
00:05:36,960 --> 00:05:37,920
there will be hope.

117
00:05:41,840 --> 00:05:43,780
This was the predecessor of

118
00:05:43,780 --> 00:05:46,720
(Chengyi Charitable Children's Home)
the Minghui-founded children's home.

119
00:05:47,440 --> 00:05:51,120
That's also where I adopted Wanxin.

120
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:54,120
Girl, what is your name?

121
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:56,160
The other kids call me Yi.

122
00:05:56,160 --> 00:05:57,200
"Yi" as in memory.

123
00:05:57,360 --> 00:05:58,320
What a good girl.

124
00:05:59,160 --> 00:06:02,320
From now on, you're my little girl.

125
00:06:03,440 --> 00:06:05,680
"The bluebird brings
no news from beyond the clouds,

126
00:06:06,520 --> 00:06:10,040
yet letters are sent
across thousands of peaks."

127
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:12,200
How about calling you Wanxin?

128
00:06:12,640 --> 00:06:13,680
If I'm called Wanxin,

129
00:06:13,680 --> 00:06:15,560
will I have a grandpa from now on?

130
00:06:16,440 --> 00:06:18,000
Such a good girl.

131
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:21,560
So it was because of them

132
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:24,320
that I was able to meet you.

133
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:28,680
It was all destiny.

134
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:33,760
I'm telling you this today

135
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:35,400
because I hope

136
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:38,800
you can carry on the charitable work

137
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:40,960
of Minghui Group.

138
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:43,800
Don't worry, Grandpa.

139
00:06:44,360 --> 00:06:47,640
We will work hard to be as good as you.

140
00:06:48,960 --> 00:06:50,120
I believe

141
00:06:50,920 --> 00:06:54,760
(Engagement Certificate)
you will do even better than I did.

142
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:01,320
Grandpa,

143
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:03,840
what happened to them later?

144
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:10,920
Miss Lin's father was persecuted.

145
00:07:12,760 --> 00:07:17,680
Mr. Shen had to protect
the supply transport routes.

146
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:19,920
My father-in-law and I

147
00:07:21,520 --> 00:07:23,560
were prepared to
sacrifice ourselves long ago.

148
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:25,560
I will assist you
with everything I have.

149
00:07:26,520 --> 00:07:27,800
But from now on,

150
00:07:28,840 --> 00:07:31,200
no one will know your true identity.

151
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,800
We must hide it from everyone,

152
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:35,640
including Shuyi.

153
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:54,050
Mr. Shen pretended to
accept the appointment.

154
00:07:54,050 --> 00:07:55,520
Congratulations, Mr. Shen, on becoming
the Chamber of Commerce president.

155
00:07:55,520 --> 00:07:59,040
(Letter of Appointment)
He chose to hide the truth from Miss Lin.

156
00:08:00,320 --> 00:08:01,160
It was you.

157
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:04,960
You had people hide
the news of my father's death.

158
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:06,840
Yes.

159
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:10,920
You were the one who took
away the Lin family business.

160
00:08:12,280 --> 00:08:12,960
Yes.

161
00:08:15,320 --> 00:08:18,160
And you're the new President of
the Sino-Japanese Chamber of Commerce.

162
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:21,760
Yes.

163
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:26,440
I

164
00:08:27,960 --> 00:08:29,880
will sever all ties with you
from this moment on.

165
00:08:31,200 --> 00:08:32,120
In life or death,

166
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:34,760
we are nothing to each other.

167
00:08:38,560 --> 00:08:44,360
From then on,
Miss Lin broke off with Mr. Shen.

168
00:08:47,880 --> 00:08:48,680
I don't understand.

169
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:51,040
Today,

170
00:08:51,680 --> 00:08:53,840
why didn't you let me tell Miss Lin?

171
00:08:55,480 --> 00:08:57,400
You clearly could have told her.

172
00:08:57,400 --> 00:09:00,160
Because if you did,
she would stay by our side.

173
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:02,800
I couldn't bear to.

174
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:11,620
Later, Miss Lin kept
raising funds for the front lines.

175
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:14,920
The situation was very dangerous.

176
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:17,080
You're injured.

177
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:22,840
Mr. Shen, you should be more careful.

178
00:09:24,760 --> 00:09:25,680
Are you worried about me?

179
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:29,560
I'm not the only one
who wants to kill you now.

180
00:09:30,760 --> 00:09:32,160
I'm just afraid you'll die
at someone else's hands.

181
00:09:40,680 --> 00:09:41,680
You're crazy!

182
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:43,960
Since you chose this path,

183
00:09:45,040 --> 00:09:47,000
you should know there's
no longer a chance for us.

184
00:09:56,920 --> 00:09:57,840
Mr. Shen,

185
00:09:58,160 --> 00:10:01,360
those people were clearly
there to assassinate Miss Lin.

186
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:03,960
Why don't you just tell her the truth?

187
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:07,360
Tell Miss Lin to protect herself.

188
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:11,160
She knows exactly what her situation is.

189
00:10:13,160 --> 00:10:15,600
But for every extra
charity voucher she sells,

190
00:10:16,520 --> 00:10:19,000
the front line gets 30 more boxes
of medical supplies.

191
00:10:21,520 --> 00:10:22,840
Shuyi will not give up.

192
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:25,000
But what about you, sir?

193
00:10:29,560 --> 00:10:30,000
Me?

194
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:36,360
I'm neither man nor ghost now.

195
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:38,160
If she's involved with me,

196
00:10:39,240 --> 00:10:41,200
it will only bring
more danger to her life.

197
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:44,640
I understand everything you're saying.

198
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:47,800
It's just a bit hard to accept.

199
00:10:56,560 --> 00:10:59,040
Miss Lin was repeatedly targeted.

200
00:10:59,640 --> 00:11:02,200
Even though Mr. Shen arrived in time,

201
00:11:02,960 --> 00:11:06,360
they were separated by
layers of misunderstandings

202
00:11:06,680 --> 00:11:08,960
and unspeakable hardships.

203
00:11:27,840 --> 00:11:31,960
The organization ordered Miss Lin
to Gang City to continue her work.

204
00:11:32,760 --> 00:11:34,400
No one expected

205
00:11:35,840 --> 00:11:41,480
that this farewell would be
the last time they saw each other.

206
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:19,600
Sir, the situation is tense right now.

207
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:21,160
Aren't you coming with me?

208
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:28,160
I have more important things to do.

209
00:12:29,360 --> 00:12:30,200
Mr. Shen,

210
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:34,200
I will tell Miss Lin everything.

211
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:38,160
Qianmo,

212
00:12:41,560 --> 00:12:43,160
if I don't make it to Gang City,

213
00:12:45,560 --> 00:12:46,400
don't tell Shuyi

214
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:48,360
about my affairs.

215
00:12:52,560 --> 00:12:54,520
And don't give
those things to her anymore.

216
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:02,240
I won't.

217
00:13:03,160 --> 00:13:04,200
I definitely won't.

218
00:13:07,800 --> 00:13:08,800
Mr. Shen,

219
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:13,160
Miss Lin and I
will wait for you in Gang City.

220
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:17,400
Go on.

221
00:13:19,680 --> 00:13:25,160
♪Blending with letters left unread
drifting through the air♪

222
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:31,240
♪You turn and look back at me♪

223
00:13:32,680 --> 00:13:37,880
♪In those same eyes familiar tears
quietly appear♪

224
00:13:39,040 --> 00:13:44,360
♪It feels like we have carried so much♪

225
00:13:45,960 --> 00:13:51,120
♪So many questions time itself
could not make clear♪

226
00:13:52,560 --> 00:13:57,560
♪The moment you walked into my life♪

227
00:13:59,040 --> 00:14:04,520
♪Every dream I had became something
I want with you near♪

228
00:14:05,240 --> 00:14:11,880
♪How many letters have I written
just for you?♪

229
00:14:36,020 --> 00:14:41,500
♪Tonight the rain falls soft and slow♪

230
00:14:43,100 --> 00:14:48,580
♪Blending with letters left unread
drifting through the air♪

231
00:14:49,620 --> 00:14:54,660
♪You turn and look back at me♪

232
00:14:56,100 --> 00:15:01,300
♪In those same eyes familiar tears
quietly appear♪

233
00:15:02,460 --> 00:15:07,780
♪It feels like we have carried so much♪

234
00:15:09,380 --> 00:15:14,540
♪So many questions time itself
could not make clear♪

235
00:15:15,980 --> 00:15:20,980
♪The moment you walked into my life♪

236
00:15:22,460 --> 00:15:27,940
♪Every dream I had became something
I want with you near♪

237
00:15:28,660 --> 00:15:35,300
♪How many letters have I written
just for you?♪

238
00:15:35,740 --> 00:15:41,100
♪If only you could truly hear
what my heart is trying to say♪

239
00:15:42,100 --> 00:15:48,180
♪From this life on
no distance could keep us apart♪

240
00:15:48,460 --> 00:15:51,180
♪The promise we made♪

241
00:15:51,340 --> 00:15:54,820
♪Will find its way to be fulfilled
one day♪

242
00:15:55,020 --> 00:16:01,420
♪But I want more
than just that fleeting gaze♪

243
00:16:01,620 --> 00:16:07,700
♪Still I have not heard your answer♪

244
00:16:08,420 --> 00:16:14,500
♪Can we still rewrite the ending
we face?♪

245
00:16:14,740 --> 00:16:19,540
♪When regrets begin to turn around you
will hear it all♪

246
00:16:20,340 --> 00:16:23,020
♪Everything that leads me back to you♪
